He
felt
much
cast
down
almost
hopeless.
On
his
entrance
his
wife
served
out,
in
orderly
sort,
such
dinner
as
she
had
to
give
him
and
the
bairns.
It
was
only
porridge,
and
too
little
of
that.
Some
of
the
younger
children
asked
for
more
when
they
had
done
their
portion
an
application
which
disturbed
William
much.
While
his
wife
quieted
them
as
well
as
she
could,
he
left
his
seat
and
went
to
the
door.
He
whistled
a
cheery
