from
gathering
on
the
lids
of
his
gray
eyes,
and
plashing
thence
to
the
threshold.
He
cleared
his
vision
with
his
sleeve,
and
the
melting
mood
over,
a
very
stern
one
followed.
He
still
stood
brooding
in
silence,
when
a
gentleman
in
black
came
up
a
clergyman,
it
might
be
seen
at
once,
but
neither
Helstone,
nor
Malone,
nor
Donne,
nor
Sweeting.
He
might
